Italy: First Dacian War: Rome invaded Dacia. Second Battle of Tapae: Dacian forces retreated from contact with the Romans at Tapae.
Philippine: Since at least the 3rd century, the indigenous peoples were in contact with other Southeast Asian and East Asian nations.Fragmented ethnic groups established numerous city-states formed by the assimilation of several small political units known as barangay each headed by a Datu or headman (still in use among non-Hispanic Filipino ethnic groups) and answerable to a king, titled Lakan and Rajah.
